Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine orange-red; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '60'. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 116, 12 Name Timotheos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1110)
